        "subject": "LU-1672 obdclass: Set correct ldd_fsname when using osd-zfs",
        "message": "LU-1672 obdclass: Set correct ldd_fsname when using osd-zfs\n\nWhen mounting a ZFS-based OST, lsi_prepare() always set ldd_fsname to\n\"lustre\".  This causes the OST to register to an incorrect Lustre file\nsystem if the user has designated it to a file system with a different\nname.  This patch fills ldd_fsname according to ldd_svname instead.\n\nChange-Id: Ib93925dd27659d6c745a0e432a4a505aa2726f99\nSigned-off-by: Li Wei <liwei@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
